From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: conda-forge feedstock <noreply@conda-forge.org>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Statically link rocksdb (and pull in its compression deps)

ifcopenshell statically embeds rocksdb in libIfcParse.a / libIfcGeom.a
because rocksdb's shared library only exposes the C API (c.h), not the
C++ API (db.h) ifcopenshell uses. See ifcopenshell's CMakeLists.txt
and https://github.com/facebook/rocksdb/issues/981.

Downstream consumers therefore can't safely depend on a dynamic
librocksdb.so — that would create two rocksdb instances in the same
process and ODR conflicts. Link against the static librocksdb.a
instead so we end up with a single consistent rocksdb in the final
extension module. snappy / lz4 / zstd are rocksdb's own compression
deps and surface once we pull rocksdb in statically; they're safe to
link dynamically.

To be removed once upstream adacpp adds rocksdb to deps_ifc.cmake.
---
 cmake/deps_ifc.cmake | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/cmake/deps_ifc.cmake b/cmake/deps_ifc.cmake
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/cmake/deps_ifc.cmake
+++ b/cmake/deps_ifc.cmake
@@ -5,4 +5,11 @@ list(APPEND
         ADA_CPP_LINK_LIBS
         IfcParse
         IfcGeom
 )
+
+# rocksdb is statically embedded in libIfcParse.a / libIfcGeom.a (see
+# ifcopenshell's CMakeLists, facebook/rocksdb#981). Link the static
+# archive to avoid two rocksdb copies in the final binary, plus its
+# compression deps dynamically.
+find_library(ROCKSDB_STATIC_LIB NAMES librocksdb.a REQUIRED)
+list(APPEND ADA_CPP_LINK_LIBS ${ROCKSDB_STATIC_LIB} snappy lz4 zstd)
